-- European Stocks Drop as Michelin Plunges; U.S. Futures, Asian Shares Fall
-- B y   D a v i d   M e r r i t t
-- 2010-09-28T07:06:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/european-stocks-drop-as-michelin-plunges-u-s-futures-asian-shares-fall.html
European stocks fell, sending the
Stoxx Europe 600 Index lower for a second day, as Michelin &
Cie. tumbled after saying it will raise 1.2 billion euros ($1.6
billion) in a rights offer. U.S. futures and Asian shares
declined.  The benchmark Stoxx 600 fell 0.5 percent to 261.69 at 8:04
a.m. in London, extending yesterday’s 0.4 percent retreat.
Michelin, the world’s second-largest tiremaker, slumped 7.2
percent. Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index fell 0.3
percent, while the MSCI Asia Pacific Index lost 0.6 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at 
